Steps to install dev environment:
=================================
If on Mac OSX:
1. brew install node
2. brew install npm
3. brew install mongodb

Otherwise:
* node.js: https://docs.npmjs.com/getting-started/installing-node
* mongodb: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-os-x/#install-mongodb-community-edition

Steps to run dev environment:
=============================
1. sudo mongod [--dbpath .]
2. npm start
3. Go to http://localhost:3000/

Notes:
- use ReactDOMServer.renderToStaticMarkup(element) to get HTML from React components